Instrument Number: 20220412000011 Document:L Rec: $205.50 Page-2 of 3
Record Date:4/12/2022 7:06 AM King County, WA
NOTICE OF CLAIM OF LIEN
NOTICE IS HEREBY GIVEN that, pursuant to the Declaration and Covenants, Conditions,
Restrictions and Reservations for South Garden Court, a condominium, recorded February 12,
1991, under King County recording number 9102120664, and all subsequent amendments and
additions thereto (the "Declaration"), the undersigned South Garden Court Condominium
Association, a Washington non-profit corporation (the "Association"), claims a lien against the real
property located at 1830 South 336th Street, Unit D201, Federal Way, King County, Washington
98003, which real property is legally described as follows:
UNIT D201 OF SOUTH GARDEN COURT, ACCORDING TO DECLARATION
THEREOF RECORDED UNDER RECORDING NO. 9102120664, RECORDS OF
KING COUNTY, WASHINGTON, RECORDED IN VOLUME 102 OF CONDOMINIUM
PLATS, AT PAGE 38 THROUGH 41, INCLUSIVE.
SITUATE IN THE COUNTY OF KING, STATE OF WASHINGTON
Assessor's Parcel No. 788070-0150
The Association claims a lien upon the above-described real property in the following amount:
Unpaid assessments, late fees, & other charges (as of 4/6/2022): $3,904.62
March 2022 attorney fees and costs:
Unofficial Copy
$45.00
April 2022 attorney fees through 4/11/22:
$350.00
Recording costs for notice of claim of lien:
$216.53
Mailing costs certified and first-class mail:
$5.31
TOTAL:
$4,521.46
together with such additional assessments, fines, charges, late fees, interest, and attorney's fees
and costs of collection as shall accrue or be imposed against the above-described real property
from the date hereof, in accordance with the Declaration, the Association's governing documents,
and RCW 64.34, without the necessity of further recording. The undersigned attorney(s) are debt
collectors for the Association and any information obtained by said attorney(s) will be used for that
purpose.
DATED this 11th day of April, 2022.
SOUTH GARDEN COURT CONDOMINIUM
ASSOCIATION
By: Dand Haks
David Huhs, Attorney for Association
Laurel Law Group, PLLC
